:: Yes, the name… [venue-colony] {"position":"1400,1050","size":"100,100"}
<div class="colony-scene">
<svg class="colony-corner tl" viewBox="0 0 28 28"><path d="M2,26 L2,5 Q2,2 5,2 L26,2" fill="none" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/><path d="M6,26 L6,9 Q6,6 9,6 L26,6" fill="none" stroke="#9a8a30" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.55" stroke-linecap="round"/><circle cx="2" cy="2" r="2" fill="#8a9a50" opacity="0.75"/><circle cx="2" cy="2" r="0.8" fill="#c8b860" opacity="0.6"/></svg>
<svg class="colony-corner tr" viewBox="0 0 28 28"><path d="M2,26 L2,5 Q2,2 5,2 L26,2" fill="none" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/><path d="M6,26 L6,9 Q6,6 9,6 L26,6" fill="none" stroke="#9a8a30" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.55" stroke-linecap="round"/><circle cx="2" cy="2" r="2" fill="#8a9a50" opacity="0.75"/><circle cx="2" cy="2" r="0.8" fill="#c8b860" opacity="0.6"/></svg>
<svg class="colony-corner bl" viewBox="0 0 28 28"><path d="M2,26 L2,5 Q2,2 5,2 L26,2" fill="none" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/><path d="M6,26 L6,9 Q6,6 9,6 L26,6" fill="none" stroke="#9a8a30" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.55" stroke-linecap="round"/><circle cx="2" cy="2" r="2" fill="#8a9a50" opacity="0.75"/><circle cx="2" cy="2" r="0.8" fill="#c8b860" opacity="0.6"/></svg>
<svg class="colony-corner br" viewBox="0 0 28 28"><path d="M2,26 L2,5 Q2,2 5,2 L26,2" fill="none" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/><path d="M6,26 L6,9 Q6,6 9,6 L26,6" fill="none" stroke="#9a8a30" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.55" stroke-linecap="round"/><circle cx="2" cy="2" r="2" fill="#8a9a50" opacity="0.75"/><circle cx="2" cy="2" r="0.8" fill="#c8b860" opacity="0.6"/></svg>
The mention of the name shocks you sober, instantly, then giddies you up to your drink again, as quickly, and being so fast makes it double.

'I know him well.'

You do. You used to wake up on the sofa in his mother's house in Highbury, when you were both twenty-two. She was a patient woman and preternaturally kind, who let you sleep there with your whisky when you couldn't go home.

'Go to see Lackland, he's surely expecting you. But don't hang about in his office, get through to the back: the password's //Valletta//. You didn't hear it from me. I'm not here. I'm in Oxford, being adored.'
(set: $knowsCopperSecret to true)\
(set: $knowsLackland to true)
<div class="lore-box">
<strong>⟡ SECRET LEARNED ⟡</strong>

Davy Merkin gave you a password: //Valletta//. For Lackland's back room.
</div>

You surface upon Dean Street.

[[Back to Dean Street|Dean Street]]
</div>

