:: Approach Shana [venue-trishas] {"position":"700,1700","size":"100,100"}
<div class="trishas-frame">
<span class="trishas-strip">· · · · · · · · · ·</span>
(set: $metShana to true)
Her lovers are always speechless, beautiful, women who seem to be chosen more for their natural indifference to words, than shocked into silence, like her male companions.

She doesn't look up but knows you're there because she has read the Angelic Keys of Edward Kelly, and has such a talent for practical magick. Drinks land on the table, all whiskys, one for each of her five companions and somehow one more for you. She is yet to look up.

'Give it here,' she says.

<span class="guided-link">[[Hand over the manuscript|Shana Reads]]</span>
[[I'd rather not|Shana Refused]]

:: Approach the novelist {"position":"500,550","size":"100,100"}
<svg class="french-rule" viewBox="0 0 300 60" width="100%" height="60" preserveAspectRatio="none"><defs><linearGradient id="frAmb" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#a06010" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="8%" stop-color="#b07020" stop-opacity="0.5"/><stop offset="50%" stop-color="#c88020" stop-opacity="0.65"/><stop offset="92%" stop-color="#b07020" stop-opacity="0.5"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#a06010" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient><linearGradient id="frLn" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="8%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0.9"/><stop offset="92%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0.9"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient></defs><rect x="0" y="10" width="300" height="40" fill="url(#frAmb)" opacity="0.4"/><line x1="20" y1="10" x2="280" y2="10" stroke="url(#frLn)" stroke-width="1.5"/><line x1="20" y1="50" x2="280" y2="50" stroke="url(#frLn)" stroke-width="1.5"/><g opacity="0.3" stroke="#c8a86a" stroke-width="0.6" fill="none"><line x1="40" y1="10" x2="40" y2="50"/><line x1="55" y1="10" x2="55" y2="50"/><line x1="70" y1="10" x2="70" y2="50"/><line x1="85" y1="10" x2="85" y2="50"/><line x1="100" y1="10" x2="100" y2="50"/><line x1="115" y1="10" x2="115" y2="50"/><line x1="185" y1="10" x2="185" y2="50"/><line x1="200" y1="10" x2="200" y2="50"/><line x1="215" y1="10" x2="215" y2="50"/><line x1="230" y1="10" x2="230" y2="50"/><line x1="245" y1="10" x2="245" y2="50"/><line x1="260" y1="10" x2="260" y2="50"/></g><g opacity="0.55"><path d="M130,30 Q135,14 140,30 Q145,46 150,30 Q155,14 160,30 Q165,46 170,30" fill="none" stroke="#c8a86a" stroke-width="1.2"/><circle cx="130" cy="30" r="2" fill="#c8a86a" opacity="0.7"/><circle cx="170" cy="30" r="2" fill="#c8a86a" opacity="0.7"/></g><polygon points="150,22 154,30 150,38 146,30" fill="#c8a86a" opacity="0.6"/><g opacity="0.35"><rect x="62" y="20" width="6" height="20" rx="1" fill="#002395"/><rect x="73" y="19" width="7" height="22" rx="1" fill="#f0f0f0"/><rect x="85" y="20" width="5" height="20" rx="1" fill="#ed2939"/><rect x="210" y="20" width="6" height="20" rx="1" fill="#002395"/><rect x="221" y="19" width="7" height="22" rx="1" fill="#f0f0f0"/><rect x="233" y="20" width="5" height="20" rx="1" fill="#ed2939"/></g><path d="M20,10 Q20,8 22,8 L28,8 Q30,8 30,10" fill="none" stroke="#c8a86a" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5"/><path d="M270,10 Q270,8 272,8 L278,8 Q280,8 280,10" fill="none" stroke="#c8a86a" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5"/><path d="M20,50 Q20,52 22,52 L28,52 Q30,52 30,50" fill="none" stroke="#c8a86a" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5"/><path d="M270,50 Q270,52 272,52 L278,52 Q280,52 280,50" fill="none" stroke="#c8a86a" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5"/></svg>

There, sitting quietly at a table in the corner, you spot what you're after.

He's a novelist now, though you've known him since he was only a poet.

Between the ground you've taken and his position falls an amber monolith, through the window onto Dean Street; a thick and molten bar on the gnarly floor, light and distinct. If you lingered in it you'd become a fossil, like the filoplume of a silent dinosaur.

You once told him that he should stick to poems.

So now, have you got anything to lose?

[[Nothing|The novelist]]
(link: "Everything")[(set: $confidence to $confidence - 12)(goto: "Dean Street")]

