You find it after some looking, where you always knew it was: the Chinese Fish and Chips.

You're eating at the counter when somebody passes the window: that's Lily.

(if: $tookLily1 is false)[|lily1>[(display: "Lily SVG")]\
(click-replace: ?lily1)[(set: $lilyCount to $lilyCount + 1)(set: $tookLily1 to true)(display: "Lily SVG")<span class="lily-glimpse lily-fade">That must be her, as tall as the Amazon; her joints articulate how you remember.</span>]](else:)[<div class="lily-taken">(display: "Lily SVG")</div>]

For a few minutes, you are nobody. You have no manuscript. You owe nothing to anyone.

The warmth spreads through you. The fog lifts, just a little.

