<svg class="colony-fan" viewBox="0 0 300 52" width="100%" height="52" preserveAspectRatio="none"><defs><clipPath id="cf1"><rect x="0" y="0" width="300" height="50"/></clipPath><linearGradient id="cfL" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#7aaa60" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="50%" stop-color="#9a8a30" stop-opacity="0.75"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#7aaa60" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient></defs><g clip-path="url(#cf1)" opacity="0.35"><line x1="150" y1="54" x2="0"   y2="0" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="0.8"/><line x1="150" y1="54" x2="33"  y2="0" stroke="#8a9a50" stroke-width="0.8"/><line x1="150" y1="54" x2="67"  y2="0" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="0.8"/><line x1="150" y1="54" x2="100" y2="0" stroke="#9a8a30" stroke-width="0.8"/><line x1="150" y1="54" x2="133" y2="0" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="0.8"/><line x1="150" y1="54" x2="150" y2="0" stroke="#c8b860" stroke-width="1.0"/><line x1="150" y1="54" x2="167" y2="0" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="0.8"/><line x1="150" y1="54" x2="200" y2="0" stroke="#9a8a30" stroke-width="0.8"/><line x1="150" y1="54" x2="233" y2="0" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="0.8"/><line x1="150" y1="54" x2="267" y2="0" stroke="#8a9a50" stroke-width="0.8"/><line x1="150" y1="54" x2="300" y2="0" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="0.8"/></g><line x1="0" y1="44" x2="300" y2="44" stroke="url(#cfL)" stroke-width="0.6"/><line x1="0" y1="48" x2="300" y2="48" stroke="url(#cfL)" stroke-width="1.8"/><polygon points="150,41 155,45 150,49 145,45" fill="#c8b860" opacity="0.65"/><polygon points="120,45 123,48 120,51 117,48" fill="none" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.45"/><polygon points="180,45 183,48 180,51 177,48" fill="none" stroke="#7aaa60" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.45"/></svg>
(set: $sobriety to $sobriety - 12)
He's wearing a suit that was probably clean this morning, which means he's been home and changed, but now it's beginning to crumple in sympathy with his mood.

'Not interested,' he says. His audience, in parallel, is you, all skittish-pissed and needy, and the whole roiling gross of humanity, from Adam Kadmon's day to his own, wherein a man still seeks a viable interlocutor.

The accent is Anglo-Antipodean; too clipped and politic to be functional downunder, yet here in the imperial core, it strays audibly at its burnt edges into an outback.

'I read last night in Oxford. Magnificent, actually. Met a girl; pretty woman, working on a D.Phil. at Magdalen, on Shakespeare and Co. She said she'd meet me today at the Pillars.'

He drinks so you drink and landing his glass he seems to clock you for the first time again, as he draws the whole, traversable world into his intimate sphere.

'I got a bottle of claret and waited at the Pillars,' he proceeds, spitting whispers. 'She showed, sure enough. She showed and she didn't touch a drop of it. So she left and I left and now here I am.'

You're hushed. Even his silence leaves you no room to speak.

'Listen. I know what you're wanting and it's not me you're after, but let me give you advice. Do you know Martin Lackland? Office on Frith Street?'

The mention of the name shocks you sober, instantly, then giddies you up to your drink again, just as quickly, and being so fast makes it double.

'I know him well.'

You do. You used to wake up on the sofa in his mother's house in Highbury, when you were both twenty-two. She was a patient woman and preternaturally kind, who let you sleep there with your whisky when you couldn't go home.

'Go to see Lackland, he's surely expecting you. But don't hang about in his office, get through to the back: the password's //Valletta//. You didn't hear it from me. I'm not here. I'm in Oxford, being adored.'
(set: $knowsCopperSecret to true)\
(set: $knowsLackland to true)
<div class="lore-box">
<strong>⟡ SECRET LEARNED ⟡</strong>

Davy Merkin gave you a password: //Valletta//. For Lackland's back room.
</div>

[[Back to Dean Street|Dean Street]]
