<!-- Swinging bulb -->
<div class="cellar-bulb-wrap">
<svg width="48" height="90" viewBox="0 0 48 90"><!-- Wire from ceiling --><line x1="24" y1="0" x2="24" y2="30" stroke="#888878" stroke-width="1.4" opacity="0.75"/><!-- Socket cap --><rect x="17" y="28" width="14" height="10" rx="2.5"fill="rgba(80,78,65,0.9)" stroke="rgba(160,155,120,0.7)" stroke-width="1"/><!-- Socket ring detail --><rect x="19" y="36" width="10" height="3" rx="1"fill="none" stroke="rgba(150,145,110,0.55)" stroke-width="0.8"/><!-- Outer glow halo --><ellipse cx="24" cy="60" rx="20" ry="22"fill="rgba(255,245,160,0.12)"/><!-- Bulb body — pear shape, bright and solid --><path d="M24,38 C16,38 10,45 10,55 C10,67 16,78 24,78 C32,78 38,67 38,55 C38,45 32,38 24,38 Z"fill="rgba(255,252,210,0.95)" stroke="rgba(220,210,160,0.6)" stroke-width="0.8"/><!-- Inner warm core --><ellipse cx="24" cy="57" rx="9" ry="11"fill="rgba(255,240,120,0.55)"/><!-- Filament — W-shape --><path d="M18,60 L20,53 L24,58 L28,53 L30,60"fill="none" stroke="rgba(255,200,40,0.95)" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linejoin="round"/><!-- Neck base ring --><rect x="20" y="75" width="8" height="3" rx="1"fill="rgba(200,195,155,0.65)" stroke="none"/></svg>
</div>
<div class="cellar-scene">
<div class="cellar-light"></div>
Copper gets closer.

'I asked you a question,' he says.

Quiet Frankie still hasn't looked up but Ashton Granger has; she's stopped doodling.

[[Try to run for the stairs|Fight starts]]
[[Stand your ground|Stand your ground]]
</div>

:: Alba Complete {"position":"1550,50","size":"100,100"}
London is all before you: Tyburn, Bloomsbury, Fitzrovia; St. Giles, at your feet; and Soho, which has dulled your soul and dressed you for the sun in midnight's cloak, throbs low and still, its bruised capillaries.
You found the poem, the path to dawn's bleak Albion.
Traveller, wake!

[[·|White page]]

:: Late Lily {"position":"1600,50","size":"100,100"}
You see yourself walking to meet you, he looks at you, with a pitying grin, then turns and heads, quickly, towards Centre Point.

[[Follow him|Approach Centre Point]]

:: Alba Incomplete {"position":"1550,100","size":"100,100"}
London is all before you: Tyburn, Bloomsbury, Fitzrovia; St. Giles, at your feet; and Soho, which has dulled your soul and dressed you for the sun in midnight's cloak, throbs low and still, its bruised capillaries.
You did not find the poem. The dawn will come regardless.
Traveller, sleep!

[[·|Black page]]

:: Centre Point {"position":"1650,75","size":"100,100"}
(if: ($alba contains $alba1) and ($alba contains $alba2) and ($alba contains $alba3))[(goto: "Alba Complete")](else:)[(goto: "Alba Incomplete")]

:: Dawn {"position":"1700,100","size":"100,100"}
(if: ($alba contains $alba1) and ($alba contains $alba2) and ($alba contains $alba3))[Here you are, on Dean Street again, watching the light as it peels through its changes. First cobalt; then the brassic crown that grows rich and gilded; then the antiseptic mint while the corolla rises and blooms through the lobes (frontal, parietal, temporal, occipital), the blue-blooded, hemorrhaging sky. Then the cool white quivering lip of the dawn's bells and flowers when they're trying to settle.

You have been awake for so long.

From the impossible door, Lackland emerges and cries, 'Tomorrow! Tomorrow!' as he crabwalks himself to a cab.

Yes, maybe tomorrow but till then you'll lie with Aoifa and she'll lie with you, and together you'll raise a daughter.

Better not tomorrow.

<div class="alba-final">
<em>$alba1</em>
<em>$alba2</em>
<em>$alba3</em>
</div>

And the last weight peeled from the dawn is as breathlike as a petal of the lily-of-the-valley which, caught on a thermal, is rising plum into the sun, till the days settles up and it's lost. You've forgotten the name of that flower.

Go home, make love.

FINIS]

:: Dean Street {"position":"900,400","size":"100,100","tags":"hub"}
