:: Shana Reads [venue-trishas] {"position":"900,1700","size":"100,100"}
<div class="trishas-frame">
<span class="trishas-strip">· · · · · · · · · ·</span>

She knocks //(print: $bookTitle)// to the floor and then very carefully places it back on the table, being certain to alter the page that it fell on. She reads.

'What's wrong with it?' she asks.

[[What?|Shana's Verdict]]

:: Shana Refused [venue-trishas] {"position":"500,1700","size":"100,100"}
<div class="trishas-frame">
<span class="trishas-strip">· · · · · · · · · ·</span>

'Wise,' she says. 'Or cowardly. The two are so often the same thing wearing different hats.'

She waves you away. A flick of the wrist; a whole dismissal in the gesture. The circle closes behind you like water.
(set: $confidence to $confidence - 12)
[[Back to the bar|Trisha's]]

:: Shana's Verdict [venue-trishas] {"position":"900,1850","size":"100,100"}
<div class="trishas-frame">
<span class="trishas-strip">· · · · · · · · · ·</span>

'Nothing,' she says. 'That's the thing. Nothing is wrong with it. It's just nothing.'

She pushes it back towards you. You return it to your bag like something injured.

'I love you but you need to get to work. Bring it to me six months down the line.'
(set: $confidence to $confidence + 8)
[[Take the manuscript|After Shana]]

:: After Shana [venue-trishas] {"position":"900,1950","size":"100,100"}
<div class="trishas-frame">
<span class="trishas-strip">· · · · · · · · · ·</span>

You lift a heavier bag because you are weaker, less than you were. But six months is an age, the kid will be walking by then. You smile and you leave.

