:: Jeffrey Bernard's Cow {"position":"700,1200","size":"100,100"}
<svg class="coach-beam" viewBox="0 0 300 36" width="100%" height="36" preserveAspectRatio="none"><defs><linearGradient id="wdA" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#3a2408" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="10%" stop-color="#5c3810" stop-opacity="1"/><stop offset="90%" stop-color="#5c3810" stop-opacity="1"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#3a2408" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient><linearGradient id="wdB" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#3a2408" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="10%" stop-color="#7a5220" stop-opacity="0.7"/><stop offset="90%" stop-color="#7a5220" stop-opacity="0.7"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#3a2408" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient><linearGradient id="brA" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#c8922a" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="50%" stop-color="#c8922a" stop-opacity="0.7"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#c8922a" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient></defs><rect x="0" y="6" width="300" height="24" fill="url(#wdA)"/><line x1="0" y1="6" x2="300" y2="6" stroke="url(#wdB)" stroke-width="1.2"/><line x1="0" y1="30" x2="300" y2="30" stroke="url(#wdB)" stroke-width="1.2"/><line x1="0" y1="18" x2="300" y2="18" stroke="url(#brA)" stroke-width="1.5"/><circle cx="50" cy="18" r="4" fill="#c8922a" opacity="0.5"/><circle cx="150" cy="18" r="4.5" fill="#c8922a" opacity="0.55"/><circle cx="250" cy="18" r="4" fill="#c8922a" opacity="0.5"/></svg>
'Will you do something about this cow?'

Said Jeffrey Bernard.

You take its bridle. It sneezes. When you look back he's disappeared to a timeshare on the seacoast of Bohemia.

(if: not ($haunts contains $haunt3))[(if: $hauntExplained is false)[(set: $hauntExplained to true)
<div class="lore-box">
<strong>⟡ HAUNTS ⟡</strong>

Tonight, Soho will mark you. Here, in our dream, we call these marks 'haunts'. You'll gather them as you wander the night and its stages. Seek them: you'll need them to get out.
</div>]
(set: $haunts to $haunts + (a: $haunt3))

<div class="haunt-box">
<div class="haunt-header">⟡ HAUNT COLLECTED ⟡</div>
<div class="haunt-name">THE BEAST</div>
<div class="haunt-description">Is it New York or New Year?</div>
</div>]

What will you do with his cow?

[[Ride the beast|Ride Jeffrey Bernard's cow]]

:: LINE 1 {"position":"700,200","size":"100,100"}
(set: $alba to $alba + (a: $alba1))
(set: $albaGiven's red to true)\
(set: $albaRevealed to true)
'You'll not sell it,' says Red. 'Forget the writing. That's no way to live.' As he turns from his ginger light, he kisses you and as he does you close your eyes. He is still speaking. Inside their shuttered lids you read:

<div class="revelation-box alba-fade-first">
<em>"$alba1"</em>
</div>

<strong class="alba-counter alba-fade-first">THE FIRST LINE OF THREE</strong>

[[Dream On|Alba Revealed]]

:: Alba Revealed {"position":"900,200","size":"100,100"}
<div class="quest-box">
<div class="quest-header">⟡ ALBA ⟡</div>
<div class="quest-description">
There are three lines of an aubade out in the darkness. Find them before dawn and you'll get out alive.

Miss them and you'll be another Dean Street dream.
</div>
<div class="quest-objective">FIND THE THREE LINES BEFORE DAWN</div>
</div>

[[Back to Dean Street|Dean Street]]

:: Green Sea Approach {"position":"850,200","size":"100,100"}
<div id="gs-approach"></div>[[·|LINE 2]]

:: LINE 2 {"position":"900,200","size":"100,100"}
Just off the beach is a bar called The Green Sea. It's mostly old men playing cribbage, and on its wall is a portrait of Ban Ali, though standards have slipped or morals have grown less important; there are women here now, white women, at least.

At the back round the second biggest table is a family you know, playing cards with an Italian deck.

Among them, with his back to you, is your old friend. The eldest of the kids. You see him before he sees you.

(link: "Listen")[(set: $alba to $alba + (a: $alba2))
(set: $albaGiven's street2 to true)
He speaks. The family roars on around, as his old sister winds a trick, him but you hear only this:

<div class="revelation-box">
<em>"$alba2"</em>
</div>
<span class="lily-thought">North Quad, St. John's College, Oxford. Late May night and the sexy airs of summer, the trees' munificence. Her staircase and then her, footsteps away. And in the night-blown roses of your ears, repeating what you've learned for your exams:

//Annihilating all that's made
To a green thought in a green shade.//</span>

<strong class="alba-counter">THE SECOND LINE OF THREE</strong>

[[Return to Dean Street|Dean Street]]]

:: LINE 3 {"position":"1100,200","size":"100,100"}
If dawn was something you could hear, you would hear it now. Your ears are attuned in a way that your eyes can never be. But you trust your eyes more, so the thrum of dawn approaching, registers as a silent alarm.

Then you see it, the sky tearing patches from itself and bleeding red, orange, green through the night's bandage.

(link: "Closer")[(set: $alba to $alba + (a: $alba3))
(set: $albaGiven's street3 to true)
The last line comes out of your own throat, as you cry, 'I wish that I was never…' then:

<div class="revelation-box">
<em>"$alba3"</em>
</div>

<span class="lily-thought">In a certain memory she sits on your bed, dressing; she is in her underwear, which is black and laced. It is not her beauty that stays with you or her nakedness; they struck you at the time but you've known many women after her. What changed you, under it all, was that vision of something you could not believe, made real; the perfect reality of love imagined, for the first time in your mind, as something close, that you could hold, kiss and make love to. It was the only time that life became quite real and you could not believe it. You'd burn Troy after Troy to see God's face like that again.</span>

It is written. You shall get out alive.

<strong class="alba-counter">THE THIRD LINE — THE ALBA IS COMPLETE</strong>

[[Soho!|Things turn up]]]

:: Lackland's Back Room {"position":"1200,1150","size":"100,100"}
Downstairs. A table tennis table, green as money.

Two men: Johan Clogg, bookseller. Jack Curtis, poet. 20-20. Match point.

[[Watch the decider|Watch the decider]]

:: Maltese Gangsters {"position":"1400,550","size":"100,100"}
<div class="copper-door">
<!-- Maltese cross rule — dark iron tones -->
