:: Maritime interlude {"position":"300,1000","size":"100,100"}
<div class="maritime-scene">
<div class="maritime-lamp"></div>
<div class="maritime-lightning"></div>
<span class="maritime-svg-wrap"><svg viewBox="0 0 1200 18" preserveAspectRatio="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M0,9 C25,2 50,16 75,9 C100,2 125,16 150,9 C175,2 200,16 225,9 C250,2 275,16 300,9 C325,2 350,16 375,9 C400,2 425,16 450,9 C475,2 500,16 525,9 C550,2 575,16 600,9 C625,2 650,16 675,9 C700,2 725,16 750,9 C775,2 800,16 825,9 C850,2 875,16 900,9 C925,2 950,16 975,9 C1000,2 1025,16 1050,9 C1075,2 1100,16 1125,9 C1150,2 1175,16 1200,9" fill="none" stroke="#4a7090" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.8"/></svg></span>

Turning onto Greek Street, you find yourself at sea and in a storm.

<span class="maritime-svg-wrap slow"><svg viewBox="0 0 1200 18" preserveAspectRatio="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M0,12 C30,4 60,16 90,12 C120,4 150,16 180,12 C210,4 240,16 270,12 C300,4 330,16 360,12 C390,4 420,16 450,12 C480,4 510,16 540,12 C570,4 600,16 630,12 C660,4 690,16 720,12 C750,4 780,16 810,12 C840,4 870,16 900,12 C930,4 960,16 990,12 C1020,4 1050,16 1080,12 C1110,4 1140,16 1170,12 C1200,4 1200,16 1200,12" fill="none" stroke="#3a5a78" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.9"/></svg></span>

The broiling waters shred your ship till it's leaf-tobacco, toss it like a stub.

<span class="maritime-svg-wrap"><svg viewBox="0 0 1200 18" preserveAspectRatio="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M0,9 C25,2 50,16 75,9 C100,2 125,16 150,9 C175,2 200,16 225,9 C250,2 275,16 300,9 C325,2 350,16 375,9 C400,2 425,16 450,9 C475,2 500,16 525,9 C550,2 575,16 600,9 C625,2 650,16 675,9 C700,2 725,16 750,9 C775,2 800,16 825,9 C850,2 875,16 900,9 C925,2 950,16 975,9 C1000,2 1025,16 1050,9 C1075,2 1100,16 1125,9 C1150,2 1175,16 1200,9" fill="none" stroke="#4a7090" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.8"/></svg></span>

A big hand splits the sky and a big voice booms:

<span class="ne-plus-ultra">NE. PLUS. ULTRA.</span>

Do you keep going?

[[Yes|Approach The Pillars]]
(if: $hasCleggBeermat is true)[[[Seek the shore|The coast of Carthage]]](else:)[//There is no present horizon.//]
</div>

:: Martin Lackland's Office {"position":"1200,1000","size":"100,100"}
(set: $exploredSinceFrench to true)\
You find the building on Frith Street, on the door: M. Lackland.

You knock and he buzzes you in. You climb two doglegs to his rooms.

He lifts the needle from his record, sinks his glass then tops it up again (more scotch and soda).

(link: "⟡ What's he listening to? ⟡")[<div class="lore-box">
On the turntable was //2 + 2 + 1 = Ponderosa Twins Plus One//, by the Ponderosa Twins Plus One, more specifically the song 'Bound', on which the producer Bobby Massey has writing credit. Massey had been with the O'Jays and would go on, after the turning of the millennium, to be listed as executive producer on a film with the Spice Girls and two films with David Beckham. But he, like the rest of that group, was from Cleveland, Ohio, in the U.S.A.

I'm writing this in February, 2026; if you're reading it you'll have lived at least a touch longer. So we'll know that Ye sample that song in 'Bound 2', when he still went by Kanye West. But Lackland knows nothing about that.

He has a Garrard 401 screwed into the wall, with an SME arm bolted on and a Shure cartridge. This means that he can play his music loudly.

He found the album at Dobell's several lunches ago, and it's hardly been silent since.
</div>]

He turns to his desk with both his elbows and setting them down individually, says, 'You were sent here by Jeffrey?'

You nod.

'Well, give it here.'

You lay //(print: $bookTitle)// down.

He reads the first page; then the last; then a page from somewhere in the middle.
(if: $confidence >= 60)[He sets it down as one might set a toddler down on the floor.

'This isn't bad. Have you got a job? A wife? How long can you give to me? You've something but there's work to do; lots of work.'

This is as close as you've come to anything.
(set: $confidence to $confidence + 15)
[[Leave|Dean Street]]]
(else:)[He sets it down.

'This isn't there.'

You knew that.
(set: $confidence to $confidence - 12)
[[Leave|Dean Street]]]

(if: $knowsCopperSecret is true)[You notice a door at the back of the office you hadn't seen before. Or perhaps you had, but now it means something.

<span class="guided-link">[[Whisper "Valletta"|Lackland's Back Room]]</span>]

:: Meet Jeffrey Bernard {"position":"700,1000","size":"100,100"}
(set: $knowsLackland to true)\
(set: $confidence to $confidence + 4)\
You're back on Dean Street.

From the direction of Leicester Square a man is approaching. He is walking a cow. He is Jeffrey Bernard.

He stops, and resumes a conversation you'd never begun:

'I'd very much like to wake up one morning with a cow of the Friesian variety and walk her down to Soho to the Coach and Horses, stopping on the way to buy twenty Players, ply her with vodkas until closing time, whip her off to an Indian restaurant, take her up to the Colony Room till 5.30 and then to the Yorkminster, Swiss Tavern, Three Greyhounds, get beaten up by Chinese waiters at midnight, have a row with the taxi driver, set the bed on fire, put it out with tears and then wake up on the floor. Could you then milk said cow? I doubt it.'

The cow regards you with milky indifference.

[[Deal with the cow|Jeffrey Bernard's Cow]]

:: Milk Jeffrey Bernard's Cow {"position":"900,1300","size":"100,100"}
You lie on the Dean Street pavement like a mechanic under a chassis, take an udder in your fist and squeeze it, gingerly.

A little warm milk plashes on your lips. It tastes of grass and moonlight and something you can't name.

'This,' you think, 'is why he is unwell.'

(set: $sobriety to $sobriety + 15)
(set: $confidence to $confidence + 10)
[[Get up and try again|Dean Street]]

:: No more {"position":"1700,300","size":"100,100"}
Centre Point is still behind you. It's been there all night long.

The way that you conceive, now, of its height is more temporal than spatial and like time but not but like space it remains impossible, merely notional; has a quality that space only attains when we imagine it infinitely.

One jumping from the top should fall forever and seem to fall as a ton of feathers falls in a perfect vacuum.

Standing here you can see London, Carthage, Liverpool and everything else.

(if: $hadPhoneCall is true)[You think of Aoife. The baby. The cold flat waiting for you with nothing in it but your failure.]

[[Lose|Black page]]

