Inish O'Flatterly clocks you, first with his eyes still downcast, then eventually as he looks up. 'You're a novelist and that wasn't a question,' he steams; it is the gentle steaming of the kettle, not that of the railway.

(if: $hasMissingPage is true)[Your hand goes to your pocket. The page. You'd almost forgotten; the night has that effect.

[[Show him the page|Return the page]]]\
(else:)[[[What book?|O'Flatterly's quest]]]

:: O'Flatterly's quest [venue-cecilcourt] {"position":"300,1850","size":"100,100"}
'Dear boy,' he burrs, 'I don't know who you are, and don't care who you are, and I don't know that I don't like what you've written; but do me a kindness, kid, and let's just assume I won't love it. Besides, there is something more important that you must do for me; that we must do together.' O'Flatterly coughs, disturbing the dust on the tome before him, agitating its thousand motes into flight, which hang over his desk like slate-grey clouds over Willesden Junction. His hair, which was blond already, seems longer and wilder now.

He slaps the manuscript like an arse and says: 'Something's missing! Page 47. It fell from my arms, yesterday night in the dusk, somewhere in Soho. I can tell that you move among monsters and thieves, one of them must have it: get it for me, please.'

(set: $knowsAboutPage to true)

<div class="lore-box">
<strong>⟡ QUEST ⟡</strong>

Inish O'Flatterly is searching for a missing page — Page 47 of an impossible manuscript. It's somewhere in Soho. Find it and return it to him.
</div>
[[I'll look for it|Dean Street]]

