(click-replace: ?lily5)[(set: $lilyCount to $lilyCount + 1)(set: $tookLily5 to true)(display: "Lily SVG")<span class="lily-glimpse lily-fade">Was that her passing the window, almost six-foot and with the gait of a newborn antelope?</span>]](else:)[<div class="lily-taken">(display: "Lily SVG")</div>]

As you walk in the bar drops down to silence, as if its speech were interrupted by a quick gasp for breath, the way a deer sometimes mistakes the wind in the grass for a wolf, stiffens, then goes about its day.

At one end of the bar are the artists; you know them, they are famous.

Stuffed into a barstool which his arsecheeks overhang, like clouds waiting to rain, is a stout man with his back to you. His leather jacket, somehow both parched and sweating, falls short at the neck, flashing a collar of labial pink.

Opposite him is the only man who clocks you, who is thin like verdaccio and hardly there at all.
(if: not ($haunts contains $haunt4))[<span class="guided-link">[[Approach|The Stranger at the French]]</span>]
(if: ($haunts contains $haunt4) and not ($haunts contains $haunt1))[[[Approach the artists|Talk to the Artists]]]
(if: ($haunts contains $haunt1) and not ($haunts contains $haunt2))[In the corner, you spot a familiar face — a novelist now, though you knew him when he was a poet.
[[Approach|Approach the novelist]]]
(if: ($haunts contains $haunt1) and ($haunts contains $haunt2))[<div class="venue-exhausted">[NOT NOW, TRY ELSEWHERE]</div>
[[Leave the French|Dean Street]]
[[The Colony Room is just round the corner.|The Colony Room Door]]]
