He looks at you like, painterly, he looked when you were his subject.

(if: not ($haunts contains $haunt1))[(if: $hauntExplained is false)[(set: $hauntExplained to true)
<div class="lore-box">
<strong>⟡ HAUNTS ⟡</strong>

Tonight, Soho will mark you. Here, in our mutual dream, we call them 'haunts'. You'll gather them as you wander the night and its stages. Seek them: you'll need them to get out.
</div>]
(set: $haunts to $haunts + (a: $haunt1))
(set: $exploredSinceFrench to false)
<div class="haunt-box">
<div class="haunt-header">⟡ HAUNT COLLECTED ⟡</div>
<div class="haunt-name">THE SKETCH</div>
<div class="haunt-description">He's been drawing you while you talk, the picture scares you.</div>
</div>]

