="7" height="22" rx="1" fill="#f0f0f0"/><rect x="85" y="20" width="5" height="20" rx="1" fill="#ed2939"/><rect x="210" y="20" width="6" height="20" rx="1" fill="#002395"/><rect x="221" y="19" width="7" height="22" rx="1" fill="#f0f0f0"/><rect x="233" y="20" width="5" height="20" rx="1" fill="#ed2939"/></g><path d="M20,10 Q20,8 22,8 L28,8 Q30,8 30,10" fill="none" stroke="#c8a86a" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5"/><path d="M270,10 Q270,8 272,8 L278,8 Q280,8 280,10" fill="none" stroke="#c8a86a" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5"/><path d="M20,50 Q20,52 22,52 L28,52 Q30,52 30,50" fill="none" stroke="#c8a86a" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5"/><path d="M270,50 Q270,52 272,52 L278,52 Q280,52 280,50" fill="none" stroke="#c8a86a" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5"/></svg>

As you approach, someone else catches your eye.

He is a skeleton, clad in leathers that serve for his skin. His suedehead veils the clean dome of a skull which, were its architecture less Roman, might seem vulnerable, but is, in its neoclassical form, more embolos than eggshell.

You know him as an old friend, from whom you are estranged over some personal business. He eyes you, raising his empty glass, then tilts his head, like a curious velociraptor, towards the bar. He is offering you a drink.

[[Accept his offer|His round]]

<svg class="french-rule" viewBox="0 0 300 24" width="100%" height="24" preserveAspectRatio="none"><defs><linearGradient id="frC" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="45%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0.55"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient><linearGradient id="frD" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="45%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0.28"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient></defs><line x1="0" y1="7" x2="300" y2="7" stroke="url(#frD)" stroke-width="0.5"/><line x1="0" y1="12" x2="300" y2="12" stroke="url(#frC)" stroke-width="1.2"/><svg x="140" y="0" width="20" height="24" viewBox="-12 -2 24 26" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"><g fill="#c8a86a" opacity="0.75"><path d="M0,15 C-3,10 -4,2 0,-1 C4,2 3,10 0,15Z"/><path d="M-1,13 C-4,10 -8,5 -9,3 C-9,5 -8,6 -6,5 C-3,8 -1,11 0,13Z"/><path d="M1,13 C4,10 8,5 9,3 C9,5 8,6 6,5 C3,8 1,11 0,13Z"/><rect x="-8" y="14" width="16" height="2.5" rx="0.5"/><ellipse cx="0" cy="20" rx="2.5" ry="2"/></g></svg></svg>

:: The coast of Carthage {"position":"100,1550","size":"100,100"}
<div id="carthage-approach"></div>[[·|Carthage shore]]

:: Carthage shore {"position":"100,1650","size":"100,100"}
You bottled it but you've found safe harbour in Carthage, which is not like you remember it at all. These days it is swamped with Romans.

Last time you were here, you recall only Scipio Aemilianus, who was your friend and student and who weeping said:

<div class="verse">
'A day will come when Ilium shall perish,<br>
And Priam and his people shall be slain.'
</div>

(link: "⟡ LORE: Carthago Delenda Est ⟡")[<div class="lore-box">
Just north of Tunis and still given succour by the natural exposition of geographies, though piecemeal these days as if it had passed through a grinder, is Carthage harbour. A levelled motte with all Africa as its bailey, the little islet lies flat as a landed coin-toss: the downward face is Hannibal's; that lodged against the sky is inscribed ROMA.

It is hard to know just when or where you are. Foam lingers at the sea's brown lip unnaturally, endures in rabid pinnacles and domes, such as suggests an admixture of plastics. Strange insects spawn into ammonia clouds and chase you where the great galleys once berthed.

Overlooking the harbour is Flaubert's house, or the house which we pretend that Flaubert knew, also in ruins. Stand by its jasmined gates of rotting iron and ask young Scipio just what he meant. He'll tell you true, this is a falling hour.
</div>]

You think about that still, sometimes, in England.

You see two paths:

On the hill a woman burns upon a pyre.

And past the beach, a little bar: The Green Sea.

[[Approach the pyre|Dido]]
(if: $haunts's length >= 3 or $hasCoin is true)[[[Go to The Green Sea|Green Sea Approach]]](else:)[//You must not, yet, go any deeper inland.//]
[[Wake from this dream|Dream to Dean]]

(if: $hasCoin is true)[//You feel the weight of the coin in your pocket.//

<div class="coin-toss-wrap">
<button class="coin-toss-btn" id="carthage-toss">Toss the Donkey.</button>
<div class="coin-stage" id="carthage-stage">
<div class="coin" id="carthage-coin">
<div class="coin-face coin-heads"></div>
<div class="coin-face coin-tails"></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="coin-result" id="carthage-result"></div>
</div>
<script>
(function(){
var btn = document.getElementById('carthage-toss');
if (!btn) return;
btn.addEventListener('click', function(){
btn.style.display = 'none';
var stage = document.getElementById('carthage-stage');
var coin  = document.getElementById('carthage-coin');
var result = document.getElementById('carthage-result');
stage.classList.add('active');
var heads = Math.random() < 0.5;
var endDeg = heads ? (360 * 4) : (360 * 4 + 180);
coin.style.setProperty('--coin-end', endDeg + 'deg');
coin.classList.add('flipping');
setTimeout(function(){
result.textContent = heads ? 'The pyre calls.' : 'You wake.';
setTimeout(function(){
var links = document.querySelectorAll('tw-link');
for (var i = 0; i < links.length; i++){
var t = links[i].textContent.trim();
if (heads && t === 'Approach the pyre') { links[i].click(); return; }
if (!heads && t === 'Wake from this dream') { links[i].click(); return; }
}
}, 1200);
}, 2200);
});
})();
</script>]

:: Dream to Dean {"position":"300,1550","size":"100,100"}
The columns dissolve. Salt air becomes petrol and rain.

You blink. You're standing on Dean Street again, shivering, unsure how long you were gone. The pavement is wet and real beneath your feet.

[[Dream On|Dean Street]]

