<svg class="pillars-lattice" viewBox="0 0 300 36" width="100%" height="36" preserveAspectRatio="none"><defs><linearGradient id="latEdge" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%"   stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="15%"  stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0.55"/><stop offset="85%"  stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0.55"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient><pattern id="dLat" x="0" y="0" width="42" height="24" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"><path d="M7,0 L14,12 L7,24 L0,12 Z" fill="rgba(160,35,25,0.26)" stroke="#5a96aa" stroke-width="1" stroke-linejoin="round"/><path d="M21,0 L28,12 L21,24 L14,12 Z" fill="rgba(185,215,235,0.07)" stroke="#5a96aa" stroke-width="1" stroke-linejoin="round"/><path d="M35,0 L42,12 L35,24 L28,12 Z" fill="rgba(28,108,52,0.22)" stroke="#5a96aa" stroke-width="1" stroke-linejoin="round"/></pattern><mask id="latMask"><rect x="0" y="0" width="300" height="36" fill="url(#latEdge)"/></mask></defs><rect x="0" y="0" width="300" height="36" fill="url(#dLat)" mask="url(#latMask)"/><line x1="0" y1="34" x2="300" y2="34" stroke="url(#latEdge)" stroke-width="1.2"/></svg>
(set: $confidence to $confidence - 12)
He nods, pulls //(print: $bookTitle)// towards him. He lights another cigarette.

The bar, which had been very loud, seems quieter now, while he reads the title page then turns immediately to somewhere in the middle.

He reads a little there, then turns again to another page and reads that too. He does this several times, while the bar is getting louder in your ears, until it seems about to drop.

'Not for me', he says. 'Have you tried America?'

You thank him, say goodbye, and make to leave but he calls you back:

'And by the way, tell Copper I said hello.'
(set: $knowsCopperWord to true)
He pauses, as if remembering something.

'Oh — and if you're ever in Cecil Court, look up the antiquarian. Queer fellow, but he knows things. Things about books that shouldn't exist.'
[[Try Dean Street again|Dean Street]]
<span class="guided-link">[[Head for the night bus|Meet Jeffrey Bernard]]</span>
</div>

:: The novelist {"position":"700,550","size":"100,100"}
